@node "History" "History"

   @{b}1.8@{ub} (12-Apr-00)

        - @{b}BUG FIXED@{ub}: The output file created while testing had big spaces
            which should have contained actual information.

        - @{b}BUG FIXED@{ub}: While recording scripts, messages sent to the ARexx
            port were ignored completely, eventually causing problems.

        - @{b}BUG FIXED@{ub}: repeated creation of scripts was nearly fatal.

        - @{b}BUG FIXED@{ub}: The file requester now actually uses the program
            directory, like the docs have always claimed.

        - @{b}NEW@{ub}: Any action resulting in a file requester appearing will now use
            the same requester, meaning any changes made to the requester
            window's size and placement will be maintained.

        - @{b}NEW@{ub}: Pressing the Abort button will now block the Progress window,
            finally giving feedback to the user that the press has been
            acknowledged.  The actual aborting will still not occur until
            the current chunk has finished, but you know...

        - @{b}NEW@{ub}: As of version 1.8, XPKatana now requires Amiga OS 3.0 or
            greater.  (You should've known this was coming...)

        - @{b}NEW@{ub}: There is now longer a 'Ratio:' section in the main window.
            When displaying information on packed files, the ratio will
            follow the Unpacked size.

        - The Progress window has been changed slightly:  The gauges have
            moved to the right-hand side, with the labels above; and the
            Filename: gadget now shows only the filename, without path, to
            keep the window as compact as possible.

        - The FONT and FONTSIZE options have been removed.  The Style Guide
            does not require applications to allow specifying its own fonts,
            recommending instead to use the user's font preferences.

        - Removed 'Delete File...' from the menu.  This feature was probably
            outside the scope of this program.

        - Changes in the ToolType handling mean XPKatana no longer reads
            its ToolTypes before parsing Shell arguments.  This behaviour,
            however, is not Style-Guide compliant, and will likely be
            restored for version 2.0.

        - More general internal revisions, shrinking XPKatana's program size
            by over 3 Kb.

        For older history, see @{"here" link Older_History}.

"You infiltrate my every hour,
you bug me like a flea."

                                  -Squeeze (Fingertips)

@endnode

@node "Older_History" "Older History"

   @{b}1.0@{ub} (08-Jan-96)

        - First public release.@{ub}


   @{b}1.1@{ub} (6-Mar-96)

        - @{b}NEW:@{ub} Can now use @{"xfdmaster.library" link "About_Xfdmaster" 0} to unpack files packed with
               non-XPK packers.  Also added new option to turn this on/off.

        - @{b}NEW:@{ub} Preferences moved to a separate window.

        - @{b}NEW:@{ub} ARexx commands @{"SETTMPDIR" link "ARexx_SETTMPDIR" 0}, @{"SETPUBSCREEN" link "ARexx_SETPUBSCREEN" 0} and @{"ISPACKED" link "ARexx_ISPACKED" 0}.

        - @{b}NEW:@{ub} Tooltypes/Shell arguments @{"ICONX" link "Workbench_Usage" 21} and @{"ICONY" link "Workbench_Usage" 23}, for the AppIcon
               positioning.

        - @{b}NEW:@{ub} AppIcon will now automatically determine if it must pack or
               unpack the dragged files.

        - @{b}NEW:@{ub} Clicking on "ProcessAS" while having a file queue will now
               ask you to select an output path.

        - @{b}BUG FIXED:@{ub} GETFLAG and SETFLAGS were broken.

        - @{b}BUG FIXED:@{ub} If a packing was aborted, will no longer complain
                     that the resulting file is larger than the original.

        - @{b}BUG FIXED:@{ub} A typo prevented the german install script to work
                     from the Workbench.

        - @{b}BUG FIXED:@{ub} Unpacking with "Handle Suffix" enabled was somewhat
                     quirky.

        - Clicking on "Process" or "ProcessAs..." with no selected source
          will open a file requester, asking for it.

        - Removed the TEMPDIR tooltype/argument, since it has been moved
          to the new Preferences window.

        - Maximum password length extended upto 256 chars.

        - Compiled with the optimizer turned on.  Tell me if any weird
          problem appears.

        - General code cleanup, saved around 2-3 Kb.


   @{b}1.2@{ub} (29-May-96)

        - @{b}NEW:@{ub} "Repack" mode added.

        - @{b}NEW:@{ub} Added support for external slaves with xfdmaster.
               Note that XPKatana will now require at least v37 of this
               library, though its presence is still purely optional.

        - @{b}NEW:@{ub} 3D progress bar (oooohhh!! :)

        - @{b}NEW:@{ub} New ARexx commands: @{"REPACK" link "ARexx_REPACK" 0} and @{"BEEP" link "ARexx_BEEP" 0}.  Also added an
               "ALIENEXTERN" flag for GETFLAG/SETFLAGS.

        - @{b}NEW:@{ub} New ARexx script: DefIcons_kat.rexx.  For those using
               DefIcons, the program distributed with Nicola Salmoria's
               NewIcons.

        - @{b}BUG FIXED:@{ub} Eliminated an Enforcer hit that would happen
                     if using the Test mode without the progress window.

        - After recording a script, XPKatana will ask you if you wish to
          immediately execute it.
        
        - Better error report if an error occured while unpacking an alien
          format.

        - While writing/deleting files, XPKatana will report what its doing
          in the main window, and will busy it.  Should be nicer when
          writing on slower medias (floppies).

        - Various other minor enhancement and bugs fixed.

   @{b}1.3@{ub} (unreleased version)

        - Development taken over by Victor Ducedre.

   @{b}1.4@{ub} (27-Apr-99)

        - @{b}NEW@{ub}: Entire GUI has been redesigned:
              - Uses less space, so larger fonts should no longer be a problem.
              - keyboard equivalents for nearly all gadgets.
              - the selected packer is displayed (under 3.x) in the listview,
                not in a text gadget.

        - @{b}NEW@{ub}: Removed "Can't open xfdmaster.library" requestor.  If the
          library can't be found, the "Unpack alien" option is disabled
          instead.

        - @{b}NEW@{ub}: You can now double-click on the list of packers to open the
          settings window.

        - @{b}BUG FIXED@{ub}: No longer puts the USER library in the Packers list;
          this "library" didn't work well consistently, if at all.

        - @{b}BUG FIXED@{ub}: No longer produces ".xpk.xpk" filenames when repacking.

        - @{b}BUG FIXED@{ub}: No longer fails while generating a script with a space
          in the filename, such as "Ram Disk:foobar".

        - @{b}BUG FIXED@{ub}: Abort button in progress window no longer disables
          prematurely.

        - number of Enforcer hits removed.

        - large portions of code rearranged/restructured/removed.

   @{b}1.5@{ub} (10-Aug-99)

        - @{b}BUG UNFIXED@{ub}: USER is included in the packer list (again) if an XPK
          preferences system is active. (Thanks to Dirk Stoecker for his
          invaluable assistance in pulling my fingers out of my eyes :)

        - @{b}BUG FIXED@{ub}: When using "Process As..." in all previous versions, a
          requester stating "packed file is larger than original" would always
          write the file after packing, but left it there whether the user
          chose to abort the operation or not.  Selecting "yes" to abort will
          now delete the "packed" file.

        - @{b}BUG FIXED@{ub}: Some changes done for v1.4 broke script execution from
          the "ARexx" menu.  Fixed.

        - @{b}BUG FIXED@{ub}: Another long-standing bug maintained a lock on the public
          screen, even when iconified.  Will now lock the screen only long
          enough to open the main window, then unlock it immediately
          afterwards.  (Thanks to Luca 'Hexaae' Longone for drawing this one
          to my attention.)

   @{b}1.6@{ub} (15-Nov-99)

        - @{b}BUG FIXED@{ub}: The ARexx command EXAMINE, quite frankly, wouldn't.  This
          can be attributed on one hand to blatant stupidity, and on the other
          hand to some strangeness from the E compiler.  (Thanks to "Kev" for
          the tip.)

   @{b}1.7@{ub} (11-Jan-00)

        - @{b}NEW@{ub}: Removed the hard-coded, internal icon image used for the
          AppIcon when the program icon can't be found.  It will now use
          ENV:sys/def_tool.info.

        - @{b}NEW@{ub}: Improved font handling.  Will now try these fonts, in order:
          the font from the ToolTypes/CLI arguments (if specified), the screen
          font, and good old topaz/8.

        - @{b}NEW@{ub}: When FileID.library can't be found/opened, the file type is
          no longer listed as "<disabled>".  The 'Type:' section is simply
          left out of the GUI.

        - @{b}BUG FIXED@{ub}: Clicking gadgets in the main window while the About
          window was open would cause Enforcer hits when the About window was
          closed.  The About window will now block the main window from use.

        - @{b}BUG FIXED@{ub}: Fixed an off-by-1 error that mis-recorded the task
          priority when recording scripts.

        - many, many improvements to the efficiency and structure of the code,
          including removal of duplicate code, removal of global variables,
          more robust error checking, decrease in resources needed at startup,
          and renaming of internal routines and variables to improve
          readability and maintainability of the code.

   @{b}1.7a@{ub}

        - @{b}BUG FIXED@{ub}: New font handler caused Enforcer hits if XPKatana
          was started a second time.

        - @{b}BUG FIXED@{ub}: Handling of ".xpk" suffix was severely damaged.

        - @{b}NEW@{ub}: XPKatana now requires OS 2.1 or greater.
@endnode

@node "Future" "The Future"

    Work has started on the next generation of XPKatana, unimaginitively
called XPKatana 2.0ą.  This version will almost certainly be OS 3.x only,
and is planned to include:

  @{b}°@{ub} Localization.
  @{b}°@{ub} A compact progress window option (just the progress gauge).
  @{b}°@{ub} A newer, more modern GUI.
  @{b}°@{ub} A better preferences file format, which can save settings
    for each packer, as well as window size and position.
  @{b}°@{ub} Style-guide-compliant loading and saving of the setting file.
  @{b}°@{ub} Suggestions?  @{"Tell me" link "Contact_Me" 0}.

    Note that XPKatana has now turned into more of an excuse to improve my
coding skills than anything else, since registrations, which were never great
to begin with, have pretty much stopped.


ą - Rejected names include XPKa-two-na, XPKatscan, XPKitten, XPSauce,
Everybody Loves XPKatana, I Know What You Did Last XPKatana, www.cbs.com,
Yes We Have No XPKatanas, and XPScritti XKPolitti.
@endnode

@node "About_FileID" "About FileID.library"
   FileID.library is a shared library for identifying files by analyzing its
contents.  XPKatana has built-in support for a file identifier library because
it can help you to select a packer if you know what kind of file you're going
to pack.  It also allow you to detect if a file has already been packed by an
alien cruncher such as CrunchMania, in which case it's doubtful that XPKatana
will be able to further crunch it.  The supplied version (8.0) is able to
recognize more than 645 different filetypes.

   Under Workbench 2.1 and up, this library supports localization, although
XPKatana currently doesn't.  FileID.library will still use it when displaying
the filetype description.  The archive includes the German catalog, English
being built in the library.

   The complete release can be found on Aminet at util/libs/FIDLib80.lha

   This library has been written by Oliver Lange.  He can be reached at:

   @{b}EMail:@{ub}  bloodrock@bloody.in-berlin.de

@endnode

@node "About_Xfdmaster" "About xfdmaster.library"
    Xfdmaster.library is a freely distributable shared library, originally
written by Georg Hörmann, and currently maintained by Dirk Stoecker.  This
library allows applications using it to unpack files packed by a variety
of packers, even some obsolete ones, with a common interface.

    The complete release can be found on Aminet at util/pack/xfdmaster.lha
@endnode

